    "steps": [
      {
        "n": 1,
        "text": "Mash the banana with a fork or hand mixer, add the rest of your Wet Ingredients, and stir to combine."
      },
      {
        "n": 2,
        "text": "In a separate bowl, combine the Dry Ingredients and mix together."
      },
      {
        "n": 3,
        "text": "Pour your dry ingredients into your wet ingredients and whisk until just combined."
      },
      {
        "n": 4,
        "text": "Lightly coat a pan with oil and preheat on medium. When the pan is preheated, add enough batter to the pan to form pancakes in your desired size."
      },
      {
        "n": 5,
        "text": "After 2-3 minutes or when the bottom of the pancakes are browned, lightly spray the top of the pancakes with oil to prevent any sticking, then flip, and cook the topside."
      },
      {
        "n": 6,
        "text": "Once cooked to your liking, remove the pancakes from pan, and optionally garnish with a few slices of bananas."
      },
      {
        "n": 7,
        "text": "Time to eat."
      }
    ],
